<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-01-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="367" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d367">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Foster</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Durham</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-01-20"><hi rend="italic">January 20,
                            1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Foster, in reply to Mr. Durham’s telegram, informs him that the
                        Department will consider what is the proper course to adopt in the event of
                        an unconditional refusal of indemnity, but that while diplomatic
                        negotiations are pending the President is unwilling to have any naval
                        demonstration.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>